At IGN, our engineering culture and technology is focused on innovation, leveraging and contributing to open source, and building products that have real value for the world.</p>
<p>
<br />
The Vision</p>
<p>
&bull;We are seeking an awesome Lead Engineer (Architect Level) who can help us innovate on the front-end infrastructure for IGN Media Engineering.</p>
<p>
&bull;We have the best in class brand, and the technology to power it. This engineer will make a huge impact in charting the future of our front-end platform.</p>
<p>
<br />
What does that mean for duties?</p>
<p>
&bull;You will be designing, developing and maintaining the front-end infrastructure that sits between our users and our service-oriented architecture</p>
<p>
&bull;You will be mentoring the other engineers in best practices through code reviews, pair programming, and tech talks.</p>
<p>
&bull;You will champion the use of the platform within the team, organization and across all the groups.</p>
<p>
<br />
What will get you in the door?</p>
<p>
&bull;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, or equivalent.</p>
<p>
&bull;Understand the role a front-end platform plays in the overall success of a company.</p>
<p>
&bull;Very comfortable with PHP and a strong desire to develop in modern MVC frameworks.</p>
<p>
&bull;Solid experience with developing and launching Zend Framework applications into production.</p>
<p>
&bull;Take pride in your work - front&ndash;end infrastructure and other technical work should excite you. Helping other engineers get features to production in a more timely manner should make your day!</p>
<p>
&bull;Must demonstrate ability to adapt to various programming languages and understand the importance of using the best tool for the job. We trust you with your decisions.</p>
<p>
&bull;Caching, scaling and front-to-back performance best practices using memcache, varnish, and the request/response lifecycle.</p>
<p>
&bull;Familiar with deployment processes (using fabric, capistrano, etc.), NewRelic monitoring, Nagios alerting and figuring your way around the entire LAMP stack.</p>
<p>
&bull;Know your way around standard performance optimizations like full-page caching, plus a few unusual ones.</p>
<p>
<br />
It&rsquo;d be awesome if you have...</p>
<p>
&bull;Solid experience with unit testing and continuous integration (using git, jenkins, travis, etc.)</p>
<p>
&bull;Contributed to open source</p>
<p>
&bull;Full stack experience</p>
<p>
&bull;Done public speaking on technical topics at meetups, conferences, etc.</p>
<p>
&bull;Strong desire to invest in your technical brand</p>
<p>
&bull;Knowledge and passion for Video Games on all platforms (Console, PC, Mobile)</p>
<p>
<br />
What&#39;s the benefit for working with us?</p>
<p>
&bull;You&rsquo;ll make an impact. We reach 70MM unique users. We&rsquo;re big time, but we&rsquo;re not afraid to give you real opportunities to be epic and make a difference immediately. Learn about us at http://go.ign.com/jKOmeS.</p>
