<p>
Reporting to the Director of Marketing and Business Development, the Digital Marketing and PR Manager will focus on building awareness for AskMen&rsquo;s brand, content and products through both trade and consumer-focused PR. We are looking for more than just a pitch-person.&nbsp; The ideal candidate will be an individual who can work cross-functionally to create and execute innovative campaigns around editorial events and product launches. This opportunity affords the right candidate a rare opportunity to work for a Montreal-based international media site on projects of critical importance to its future growth.</p>
<p>
<br />
AskMen.com is based in the exciting Plateau area of Montreal, with a young and vibrant staff, we work hard and play hard. We celebrate our success but don&#39;t accept complacency. We are part of a large media company but we still think and operate like a startup.</p>
<p>
<br />
<u><strong>Responsiblities:</strong></u></p>
<p>
&bull; Conceptualize, execute and manage global media strategy for consumer &amp; trade, with a focus on US market<br />
&bull; Manage the A-Z of the trade marketing campaign for the AskMen site redesign, launching mid-summer<br />
&bull; Work with various departments and teams around the world to brainstorm, develop and bring to life strategic media campaigns in support of editorial events, product launches and sales-related events<br />
&bull; Craft all external messaging for the brand, tailored to specific audiences (from weekly content pitches to press releases)<br />
&bull; Develop and continuously organize internal media database for online, print, and broadcast outlets<br />
&bull; Communicate with all departments to identify media/content syndication opportunities<br />
&bull; Submit relevant projects for recognition and awards<br />
&bull; Work with the Global PR Manager at Ziff Davis to ensure brand positioning and manage relationships with external PR agencies<br />
&bull; Act as community liaison between AskMen&rsquo;s 16+ million readers and site<br />
&bull; Establish new, strategic brand partnerships<br />
&bull; Monitor and report on media coverage and ROI from product, editorial and event initiatives<br />
&bull; Project manage and oversee major AskMen editorial/ marketing initiatives (Top99/ Top49/ GMS)<br />
&bull; Manage marketing interns</p>
<p>
<strong><u>Requirements:</u></strong></p>
<p>
<br />
&bull; Minimum of 5 years of public relations experience in online media (in-house experience a plus)<br />
&bull; University degree in a related field<br />
&bull; Experience with media covering lifestyle brands<br />
&bull; A&nbsp; database of existing current, relevant media contacts<br />
&bull; Demonstrated history of coming up with big ideas and finding relevant ways to pitch media<br />
&bull; Strong written and verbal communication skills<br />
&bull; Ability to calculate and show ROI on outreach efforts<br />
&bull; A strong social media presence on Twitter and other social networks<br />
